##################################################
##         Command to Run the Script            ##
##################################################
1. Include all the register's name in input.txt for which coverage bins need to be generated. Commented lines ("#","\s#") and blank lines in the input.txt will be taken care by the script hqm_reg_func_cov.pl in the following lines (99-117) . 

#normal mode
% perl $MODEL_ROOT/verif/tb/hqm/scripts/hqm_reg_func_cov/hqm_reg_func_cov.pl
#debug mode (To retain intermediate outputs) 
% perl $MODEL_ROOT/verif/tb/hqm/scripts/hqm_reg_func_cov/hqm_reg_func_cov.pl debug

##################################################
##              Script Output                   ##
##################################################

Script output will be generated in following path
$MODEL_ROOT/output

## coverage module and associated define file name
1. hqm_reg_func_cov_define.sv
2. hqm_reg_func_cov_groups.sv

## Intermediate output for debug purpose
1.grepoutput.sv - Includes the output of the grep command  
2.path_defines.sv - Includes the defines of the register paths
3.register_field_define.sv - Includes the defines of the register fields 
4.coverpoints.sv - Includes the coverpoints of the register fields 

##################################################
##  Integrating Output Files in The Testbench   ##
##################################################
1. copy hqm_reg_func_cov_define.sv & hqm_reg_func_cov_groups.sv in following path
$MODEL_ROOT/verif/tb/hqm/coverage/

2. create a instance of hqm_reg_func_cov_groups.sv in hqm_tb_top.sv 
e.g. hqm_reg_func_cov_groups i_hqm_reg_func_cov_groups();
or
bind hqm_tb_top hqm_reg_func_cov_groups i_hqm_reg_func_cov_groups();

3. include hqm_reg_func_cov_define.sv & hqm_reg_func_cov_groups.sv in 
$MODEL_ROOT/verif/tb/hqm/hqm_tb_lib.hdl under -vlog_files option.

Note: coverage file is gated with "HQM_COVER_ON" define which enabled with -hqm_fcov 

4. command to build [ This is default build option in hqmv25] 
% bman -dut hqm -mc hqm -btb:mpp nodelete_flow_data" -hqm_fcov & 




##################################################
##                     About The Script         ##
##################################################
Intent of the script is to generate the covergroups for computing the coverage of the registers, This script help
verification engineer to check coverage of control and status register (or any other intended register) with 
functional covergroup, Covergroups are created for each register and Coverpoints are created for each field of the register. 




